Now, `A ⊗[k] B = ℚ[x] ⊗ ℚ M₂(ℚ) ≅ M₂(ℚ[x])`.

The image of `A` in `A ⊗[k] B` is `ℚ[x] ⊗ 1`, which consists of scalar matrices in `M₂(ℚ[x])`. Hence it is central. 

