Since `A` is commutative, `f g = g f`, so the two products are equal. 

Thus `(f ⊗ I₂)` commutes with every `(g ⊗ M)` in `A ⊗ B`, because `(f ⊗ I₂)(g ⊗ M) = (f g) ⊗ M = (g f) ⊗ M = (g ⊗ M)(f ⊗ I₂)`.

